Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto one side of a large #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over half the garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread (see pantry for amount). Set aside for now.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, tear half the @chorizo slices{50%g} into small pieces.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, tear half the chorizo slices into small pieces.

Once the onion has softened, add the chorizo pieces and remaining garlic to the pan. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high. Drain and tear the @mozzarella{1%ball}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @butter{20%g}, cooked pasta and half the mozzarella pieces into the sauce until the cheese has melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add a splash of water if the sauce is looking a little thick.

Transfer the tomato pasta to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Top with the remaining mozzarella pieces, then lay the remaining chorizo slices on top.

Pop your ovenproof dish onto the baking tray alongside the garlic ciabatta. Grill until the ciabatta is golden and the pasta is bubbling, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Grill them separately if you run out of space.

When the garlic ciabatta is ready, cut in half diagonally.

Share the pizza inspired pasta bake between your serving bowls.

Serve the garlic ciabatta alongside.

Enjoy!